# Package CSS dist sync

Several foundation packages export CSS from **`dist/`**, not from `src/`. Next.js apps import the export path (for example `@afenda/appshell/afenda-appshell.css` → `packages/appshell/dist/styles/afenda-appshell.css`).

Editing **`src/` CSS alone does not update what ERP, docs, or Storybook render** until `dist/` is refreshed.

## Affected packages

| Package | Source (edit here) | Runtime import |
|---------|-------------------|----------------|
| `@afenda/appshell` | `packages/appshell/src/styles/*.css` | `@afenda/appshell/afenda-appshell.css` → `dist/styles/` |
| `@afenda/ui` | `packages/ui/src/styles/afenda-ui.css` | `@afenda/ui/afenda-ui.css` → `dist/styles/` |
| `@afenda/metadata-ui` | `packages/metadata-ui/src/**/*.css` | `@afenda/metadata-ui/afenda-metadata-ui.css` → `dist/` |

## Required workflow after CSS edits

```bash
# Fast — copies CSS only (preferred for CSS-only changes)
pnpm sync:package-css-dist

# Scoped
pnpm sync:package-css-dist -- --package @afenda/appshell

# Full package build (TypeScript + CSS)
pnpm --filter @afenda/appshell build
```

Verify before claiming ERP/visual work is done:

```bash
pnpm check:package-css-dist-sync
```

Then refresh the app (`pnpm --filter @afenda/erp dev`) and hard-reload the browser.

## Enforcement

| Layer | Behavior |
|-------|----------|
| **lint-staged (pre-commit)** | Auto-copies `src/` → `dist/` for staged package CSS and re-stages `dist/` |
| **Cursor postToolUse hook** | Injects sync reminder after agent edits package CSS sources |
| **Cursor stop hook** | Runs `pnpm check:package-css-dist-sync` when scoped CSS sources changed |
| **Governance check** | `pnpm check:package-css-dist-sync` — use in Completion Report gates |

## Agent rules

1. **Never** edit `packages/*/dist/**/*.css` by hand — it is build output.
2. After any package CSS source edit, run **`pnpm sync:package-css-dist`** (or the package `build`) **before** ERP visual verification.
3. Include **`pnpm check:package-css-dist-sync`** in Phase 0 acceptance gates when touching listed sources.
4. Skill detail: `.cursor/skills/package-css-dist-sync/SKILL.md`

## Symptom (stale dist)

CSS rules that use package-scoped custom properties (for example `--app-shell-gap-*` under `.app-shell-root`) appear partially applied: shadcn bridge tokens work, but spacing/radius using `--app-shell-*` collapse to `0px` when the token bridge rule never reached `dist/`.

Policy source: `scripts/governance/package-css-dist-policy.mjs`
